## Developer Guide

If you are new to using `nbdev` here are some useful pointers to get you
started.

### Install FastHTML_MSOAuth in Development mode

``` sh
# make sure FastHTML_MSOAuth package is installed in development mode
$ pip install -e .

# make changes under nbs/ directory
# ...

# compile to have changes apply to FastHTML_MSOAuth
$ nbdev_prepare
```

## Usage

### Installation

Install latest from the GitHub
[repository](https://github.com/ChuckNoelke/FastHTML_MSOAuth):

``` sh
$ pip install git+https://github.com/ChuckNoelke/FastHTML_MSOAuth.git
```

or from [conda](https://anaconda.org/ChuckNoelke/FastHTML_MSOAuth)

``` sh
$ conda install -c ChuckNoelke FastHTML_MSOAuth
```

or from [pypi](https://pypi.org/project/FastHTML_MSOAuth/)

``` sh
$ pip install FastHTML_MSOAuth
```

### Documentation

Documentation can be found hosted on this GitHub
[repository](https://github.com/ChuckNoelke/FastHTML_MSOAuth)’s
[pages](https://ChuckNoelke.github.io/FastHTML_MSOAuth/). Additionally
you can find package manager specific guidelines on
[conda](https://anaconda.org/ChuckNoelke/FastHTML_MSOAuth) and
[pypi](https://pypi.org/project/FastHTML_MSOAuth/) respectively.
